HOUSE JOINT RESOLUTION 1103
By Pearson
A RESOLUTION to honor and recognize the thirty-ninth annual
Africa in April Cultural Awareness Festival in
Memphis and to commend Yvonne and David
Acey for their leadership and service to the
Memphis community.
WHEREAS, the members of this General Assembly are pleased to recognize events that
celebrate cultural heritage, promote education, and strengthen the bonds of community
throughout the State of Tennessee; and
WHEREAS, the Africa in April Cultural Awareness Festival, held annually in Memphis, is
a treasured cultural tradition that highlights the rich heritage, history, and artistic expressions of
the African continent and the African Diaspora; and
WHEREAS, in 2026, this remarkable festival celebrates its thirty-ninth anniversary,
marking nearly four decades of cultural celebration, education, and economic opportunity for
artists, performers, educators, and vendors from across the Mid-South and beyond; and
WHEREAS, the festival provides a vibrant platform for cultural exchange, offering
lectures, exhibitions, musical performances, culinary experiences, and family-centered
programming that uplift the traditions and global influence of African cultures; and
WHEREAS, Africa in April has grown into one of the largest cultural festivals in the
region, drawing thousands of residents and visitors to the City of Memphis each year and
contributing to the cultural vitality and economic development of the community; and
WHEREAS, the continued success of the Africa in April Cultural Awareness Festival is
made possible through the dedication and leadership of community advocates who believe in
the power of culture to inspire unity and understanding; and
WHEREAS, Yvonne Acey and David Acey, widely respected leaders in Memphis and
affectionately known as a Memphis power couple, have demonstrated exceptional commitment
HJR1103
015267
- 1 -

to uplifting the community and supporting initiatives that celebrate African heritage and culture;
and
WHEREAS, through their leadership, advocacy, and service, Yvonne and David Acey
have helped ensure that the Africa in April Festival continues to flourish as a beacon of cultural
pride, education, and community engagement; and
WHEREAS, it is fitting that the members of this General Assembly recognize the
significance of the Africa in April Cultural Awareness Festival and commend those who work
diligently to preserve and promote its mission; now, therefore,
BE IT RESOLVED BY THE HOUSE OF REPRESENTATIVES OF THE ONE HUNDRED
FOURTEENTH GENERAL ASSEMBLY OF THE STATE OF TENNESSEE, THE SENATE
CONCURRING, that we hereby recognize and celebrate the thirty-ninth annual Africa in April
Cultural Awareness Festival in Memphis and commend Yvonne Acey and David Acey for their
outstanding leadership, dedication, and service to the Memphis community.
BE IT FURTHER RESOLVED, that an appropriate copy of this resolution be prepared
for presentation with this final clause omitted from such copy and upon proper request made to
the appropriate clerk, the language appearing immediately following the State seal appear
without House or Senate designation.
